 circumstances.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Designing out risk – opportunities to reduce crossing risk must be taken at the design stage </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">including where </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">staff actions, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">which can be </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">prone to human error, can be automated.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Effective maintenance</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> of safety controls such as road </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">markings</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, telephones, gate restraints, signage and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">cutting back </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">vegetation </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">- this </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">will </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ensure</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> that</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> they are functioning correctly and that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">a user’s ability to see trains coming </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">is</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> not impeded. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Applying advancements in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">technology</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> - n</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ew means of identifying the position of approaching trains offers opportunities for cheaper and more effective ways of warning crossing users</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> that a train is coming, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">increasing the likelihood of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">better decision making by the user as to when i</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">t is safe to cross</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Automatin</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">g </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">crossings </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">– th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ese</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">can reduce the staff resources required</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> minimise whole life cost</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, and reduce the potential for risk arising from human error</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">More e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ffective management of trains over crossings - t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">here are opportunities to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">better manage the movement of trains over crossings</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, particularly</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> with the migration to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">E</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">uropean </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">R</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ail </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">raffic </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">M</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">anagement </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">S</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ystem</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">(ERTMS)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> as the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">future form of signalling.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> ORR will play its part in ensuring that such opportunities are exploited</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and has r</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ecently proposed a research project to look at the potential to reduce road closure time at controlled crossings through smart use of ERTMS</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">More cost effective options can also be considered where crossings </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">are</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> replaced with bridges, for example, by ins</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">talling modular footbridges</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> “off the shelf”</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> which allow Network Rail to order greater volumes thus reducing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> unit</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> cost. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:5pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">How should expenditure on improving safety at level crossings be prioritised in relation to other demands on the rail budget?</span></p><ol start="19" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:5pt 0pt 0pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">We must </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ensure that the ring-fenced funding made available to Network Rail for the purpose of reducing risk at level crossings is used in the most efficient and effective way.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="20" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The 2013 Periodic Review (PR13) is the process through which ORR</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">determines the output</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s that Network Rail must deliver and the efficient cost of delivering those outputs for the period from 1 April 2014 to 31 March 2019 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">(</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the “control period</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">” or CP5)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="21" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">On 12 June we</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> published o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ur draft determination </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">for the control period </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">which </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">sets out our package of overall decisions on PR13 for consultation. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Network Rail is required through the determination to provide a railway that is safe for passengers, the workforce and the public, provides a good service to its customers and delivers val</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ue for money for taxpayers and funder</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="22" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In our draft determination we proposed to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">set </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">n</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ew</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">output for level crossings</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> that would require </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Network Rail</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to deliver a package of projects in the control period to maximise the reduction in risk of accidents at level crossings using </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> £67m ring-fenced fund made available by the Secretary of State. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Additionally, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Scottish Ministers </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">have </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">pro</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">posed</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> a ring-fenced fu</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">nd of £10m to facilitate the closure of level crossings</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">This is an </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">enhanced</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> commitment as in previous control periods there was no specific ring fenced funding available for level crossing risk reduction</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size